-- Venezuela Policy Inaction Taking Hold With Chavez Sick: Nomura
-- B y   D a v i d   P a p a d o p o u l o s
-- 2012-04-26T18:26:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/venezuela-policy-inaction-taking-hold-with-chavez-sick-nomura.html
Policy inaction is taking hold in
Venezuela because of President Hugo Chavez’s sickness, said
 Boris Segura , a strategist at Nomura Securities International in
New York.  Venezuela’s economy will grow 5 percent at the most this
year, Segura said at the Bloomberg Latin America Investing
Conference in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
